I'm not Irish.

4
00:00:13,889 --> 00:00:15,967
it's not another one of those stereotypes:

5
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:18,584
Boston Irish Catholic bigot
living in the projects.

6
00:00:20,194 --> 00:00:21,513
well that we did..
we did live in the projects.

7
00:00:22,274 --> 00:00:23,608
My husband Bob was making $70 a week

8
00:00:23,808 --> 00:00:26,450
and half of that was going to support
the children of his first marriage.

9
00:00:27,688 --> 00:00:31,038
Yeah, he was divorced and he was 15 years older than me.

10
00:00:31,238 --> 00:00:33,784
He was my school bus driver
when I went to high school.

11
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:36,640
He asked for a bite of my Milky Way

12
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:38,987
That was the start of our courtship

13
00:00:39,501 --> 00:00:42,835
You can bet my family wasn't
delighted to see me marry him

14
00:00:45,012 --> 00:00:50,399
but he was a good man, good
husband, good father, good person.

15
00:00:51,350 --> 00:00:55,698
So, there we were,
living on $35 a week with our two girls

16
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:58,963
but remember this was 1961

17
00:00:59,163 --> 00:01:01,117
$35 went a lot farther than it does now

18
00:01:01,317 --> 00:01:02,760
Our Jack was in the White House

19
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:05,787
looked as if our country had turned a corner

20
00:01:05,987 --> 00:01:07,050
not really political, but I believed that

21
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:11,546
and our Pope, that was Pope John the 23rd at that time

22
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:15,204
said we all had to learn to live together
and I believe that too.

23
00:01:15,404 --> 00:01:17,786
And Bob believed that and he was Irish.

24
00:01:17,986 --> 00:01:21,926
When you get right down to it I'm partially Irish too.

25
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:25,136
Mostly French, but I'm partially Irish.

26
00:01:33,579 --> 00:01:39,214
Afterwards, they asked what was a woman
doing out on the streets after midnight?

27
00:01:42,082 --> 00:01:44,661
They sure let me know
they believed there was another man.

28
00:01:44,861 --> 00:01:48,093
Well, there was another man.
His name was Elvis.

29
00:01:48,293 --> 00:01:49,280
Elvis Presley.

30
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:55,903
And he had a brand new movie out and I had a
brand new four month old baby.

31
00:01:56,022 --> 00:01:57,078
I was still breastfeeding.

32
00:01:58,248 --> 00:01:59,374
It was my first time out.

33
00:02:03,650 --> 00:02:05,069
Ok, sure.

34
00:02:05,269 --> 00:02:08,661
Milky Way Aramis what would you take?

35
00:02:09,647 --> 00:02:12,024
Elvis, he drives me wild.

36
00:02:13,771 --> 00:02:16,192
...

37
00:02:16,820 --> 00:02:19,470
See you next week.

38
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:21,541
Yeah, bye
Bye

39
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,498
So would you like to do the hula-hula?

40
00:04:39,922 --> 00:04:41,106
Gerry...

41
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:43,074
I was raped..

42
00:04:44,427 --> 00:04:47,176
a colored...

43
