74
00:08:38,866 --> 00:08:41,225
Now that changes things quite a bit.

75
00:08:43,469 --> 00:08:46,180
We'll know right away, won't we?

76
00:08:46,589 --> 00:08:51,050
Not likely, it will be to be hard to tell the
race of a newborn especially in...

77
00:08:52,346 --> 00:08:54,355
I'll send the social worker in to see you.

78
00:08:54,555 --> 00:08:57,329
You started plans
to get the baby up?

79
00:08:57,529 --> 00:09:00,779
No, we haven't decided.

80
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:03,151
I mean, if it turns out to be colored.

81
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:04,931
We haven't decided.

82
00:09:05,339 --> 00:09:09,395
And how are you gonna feel every time
someone asks you about the father of this child?

83
00:09:11,245 --> 00:09:14,579
I..I don't know.

84
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,980
I'll send the social worker in.

85
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:20,180
This would be a lot easier if you don't get attached.

86
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,982
Doctor!

87
00:09:26,432 --> 00:09:29,961
I tried not to.
Believe me, I tried not to.

88
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:37,296
In the beginning I prayed to God that one of us would die.

89
00:09:41,235 --> 00:09:46,143
But eight
months is too long to close your heart

90
00:09:47,194 --> 00:09:49,164
against the... yourself living right inside you

91
00:09:52,645 --> 00:09:56,110
It's too late to say don't get
attached now.

92
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:16,446
Your brother John says she's a beautiful child.

93
00:10:18,665 --> 00:10:19,904
Have you seen her yourself?

94
00:10:20,104 --> 00:10:21,680
Have I seen her?

95
00:10:22,295 --> 00:10:24,029
I gave her my Milky Way, a first Milky way

96
00:10:24,129 --> 00:10:26,460
she's a Cummings, she really enjoyed it.

97
00:10:28,178 --> 00:10:29,802
I'm just giving the official word going home

98
00:10:31,052 --> 00:10:32,173
I like the name you pick for her, too.

99
00:10:32,373 --> 00:10:34,536
Barbra Ann it's good name, Barbra Ann Cummings

100
00:10:34,736 --> 00:10:35,548
Suits her.

101
00:10:35,748 --> 00:10:38,019
You see her knuckles?

102
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,638
Our babies come out purpose
plums

103
00:10:48,406 --> 00:10:51,404
Bob, the doctor says she's gonna stay that way.

104
00:10:57,362 --> 00:10:59,549
I think that she should be with people who look like her.

105
00:11:01,532 --> 00:11:04,568
I don't want anyone
ever to be cruel to her

106
00:11:09,401 --> 00:11:10,511
Okay.

107
00:11:12,369 --> 00:11:15,548
I told your mother we'd be coming home without the baby

108
00:11:16,787 --> 00:11:20,013
I asked her to tell the others
you were too upset to ever hear mentioned again

109
00:11:21,813 --> 00:11:23,086
They'll think she's dead.

110
00:11:25,222 --> 00:11:26,851
I suppose that's the best way to think about it.

111
00:11:29,311 --> 00:11:32,023
Are you ready?
Yes, Father.

112
00:11:42,329 --> 00:11:44,899
What name have you chosen for this child?

113
00:11:45,099 --> 00:11:46,555
Barbara Ann.

114
00:11:55,100 --> 00:12:05,008
Barbara Ann, I baptize you in the name of
the Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost, Amen.

115
00:12:13,310 --> 00:12:15,780
You see the light of Christ.

116
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:22,848
Mrs. Birrell?
Yes

117
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:38,056
Her name's Barbara Ann.
I made it.

118
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:42,491
When she's adopted,
will they let her take it with her?

119
00:13:42,691 --> 00:13:45,506
Probably, I don't have
clothes to spare.

120
00:13:45,706 --> 00:13:46,715
Can I call?

121
00:13:48,910 --> 00:13:51,621
I'm pretty sure social
services told you the rules.

122
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:10,469
I suppose you are used to this, but would you not...

123
00:14:10,669 --> 00:14:14,182
She'll be fine.
She'll be fine here.

124
00:14:23,336 --> 00:14:26,985
I have no lack of hair, no bracelet, no pictures

125
00:14:27,185 --> 00:14:29,077
none of the things you get even when your baby dies.

126
00:14:29,277 --> 00:14:31,240
So it's hard for me to remember.

127
00:14:34,219 --> 00:14:35,732
Guess I wasn't supposed to remember

128
00:14:37,247 --> 00:14:38,523
but I did...

129
00:14:39,514 --> 00:14:41,187
every single day

130
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,001
You're sure you want to do this?
Yeah

131
00:14:57,246 --> 00:15:00,405
You're shaking?
I gotta get over that now, don't I?

132
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:04,651
Can't be blamed every colored man for
what one did.

133
00:15:04,989 --> 00:15:06,575
SEGREGATION NOW!

134
00:15:13,283 --> 00:15:15,109
ALL MEN ARE CREATED EQUAL

135
00:15:15,309 --> 00:15:16,915
WE NEED BETTER SCHOOLS

136
00:15:21,934 --> 00:15:23,659
She's over 2 now.

137
00:15:23,859 --> 00:15:25,889
2 and 3/4. Almost 3.

138
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:32,569
You think we can provide the answer?

139
00:15:32,769 --> 00:15:35,096
She is in foster care,
she must have been adopted away a long time ago.

140
00:15:35,721 --> 00:15:37,337
Maybe they know where she is?

141
00:15:37,944 --> 00:15:40,969
Gerry, Barbra is gone, let her be.

142
00:15:54,815 --> 00:15:57,512
KEEP OUR COUNTRY PURE

143
00:16:26,834 --> 00:16:28,834
"We shall overcome"

144
00:16:48,591 --> 00:16:50,799
WE DEMAND FREEDOM NOW!

145
00:17:03,310 --> 00:17:08,029
Married people have secrets.
Bob and I had one.

146
00:17:08,229 --> 00:17:11,599
Its name was Barbara

147
00:17:11,699 --> 00:17:15,079
We shared it for 24 years.
We didn't talk about it much.

148
00:17:15,179 --> 00:17:19,844
After a while when Martin Luther King was murdered

149
00:17:20,044 --> 00:17:21,390
we figured what was the point:

150
00:17:21,590 --> 00:17:23,449
we were the enemy, we killed him.

151
00:17:23,649 --> 00:17:27,973
I didn't think Barbara would ever want to know us.

152
00:17:31,476 --> 00:17:32,413
Ghetto?

153
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:36,410
Well, you say ghetto to
some people and they think...

154
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:41,354
well..I don't have to tell you
what you're thinking, do I?

155
00:17:41,554 --> 00:17:44,573
But it wasn't like that when you lived inside.

156
00:17:44,773 --> 00:17:48,503
We had our doctors and lawyers, churches..

157
00:17:48,703 --> 00:17:55,572
businesses, we had community,
a good place to raise up children.

158
00:17:55,772 --> 00:17:59,138
and that's just
what I made it my business to do:

159
00:17:59,503 --> 00:18:02,180
first moan and then the abandoned ones.

160
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:07,268
I raised them up decent, God-fearing and wanted.

161
00:18:09,619 --> 00:18:11,263
Then the war came in.

162
00:18:37,510 --> 00:18:40,088
Roger, Stevie, get away from the window!
Close the curtain!

163
00:18:41,506 --> 00:18:42,640
Bob, you're okay?

164
00:18:44,069 --> 00:18:46,980
But you're holding onto Scotty so
tightly that you gonna cut off his circulation!

165
00:18:48,914 --> 00:18:50,053
Mom, I'm scared!

166
00:18:50,253 --> 00:18:51,879
Stevie! Stevie, come over here!

167
00:18:52,079 --> 00:18:53,769
Scotty, I want you to sit right over there.

168
00:18:53,969 --> 00:18:55,281
Good!

169
00:18:55,481 --> 00:18:56,800
Now you come on, Barbara Anne

170
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,060
Ellie you stay right here

171
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:00,833
I want you to hold Tracy

172
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:07,643
Then I'll hold on to you.

173
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:11,104
You see, we have nothing to be scared of,
we're all here together.

174
00:19:12,792 --> 00:19:16,477
What's going on outside of our window
everyone else needs a TV to see.

175
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,679
I want it to stop!

176
00:19:18,879 --> 00:19:23,226
Sometimes you have to mark great
trouble with great outcry.

177
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:26,990
He's dead. I never even saw him!

178
00:19:29,232 --> 00:19:32,562
I think dr. King has found
a far better home than he had here.

179
00:19:34,171 --> 00:19:37,807
I don't think there's any better
home than this, mom.

180
00:19:40,242 --> 00:19:41,980
You're right.

181
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:46,860
You are right, we are very blessed.

182
00:19:48,760 --> 00:20:00,812
Every time I feel the spirit moving in my heart

183
00:20:01,012 --> 00:20:03,310
I will pray.

184
00:20:05,775 --> 00:20:16,877
Every time I feel the spirit moving in my heart

185
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:21,092
I will wait.

186
00:20:27,061 --> 00:20:29,061
Don't push it in shoving!

187
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:32,441
There him again, mummy!

188
00:20:32,641 --> 00:20:35,312
Yeah, I think they're gonna take Larry

189
00:20:36,513 --> 00:20:37,837
Why can't we keep him?

190
00:20:38,159 --> 00:20:39,005
Come on!

191
00:20:40,164 --> 00:20:41,544
We gave him a home when he had need of it.

192
00:20:41,744 --> 00:20:43,744
If he doesn't need it anymore
they'll be others that will!

193
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,435
Now come on
let's try out this birthday bike.

194
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:50,494
How about a race?

195
00:20:51,838 --> 00:20:52,387
All right.Yeah?

196
00:20:52,587 --> 00:20:56,318
On your mark! Get ready, set, go!

197
00:21:07,344 --> 00:21:08,489
All right, that's fine enough, come back!

198
00:21:08,689 --> 00:21:09,736
Come back now!

199
00:21:17,338 --> 00:21:19,936
Shall I fix the seat for you?

200
00:21:20,136 --> 00:21:23,891
He didn't have to, he said my legs are just as long as his.

201
00:21:24,091 --> 00:21:27,066
Oh well, you certainly do have long legs!

202
00:21:27,266 --> 00:21:29,097
Has my daddy had long legs?

203
00:21:30,017 --> 00:21:31,473
I'm sure he did.

204
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:34,837
But you don't know.
No ma'am, I don't.

205
00:21:36,111 --> 00:21:38,008
What about Stevie's daddy and Roger's?

206
00:21:38,208 --> 00:21:43,164
Well, I was married to him,
of course I know what kind of legs he had!

207
00:21:43,364 --> 00:21:48,391
why am I Cummings and you all are Burrels

208
00:21:48,591 --> 00:21:49,927
Barbara, who's been talking to you?

209
00:21:50,127 --> 00:21:51,553
This boy at my school.

210
00:21:51,753 --> 00:21:57,251
He said you couldn't be my mama
cuz you and me don't have the same name.

211
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,243
You and I.

212
00:21:59,548 --> 00:22:00,665
Are you my mommy?

213
00:22:01,058 --> 00:22:02,834
Yes I'm your mommy.

214
00:22:03,066 --> 00:22:06,529
I have been your whole life.

215
00:22:06,674 --> 00:22:09,759
You didn't come out of my body
and you don't have my last name

216
00:22:11,156 --> 00:22:14,819
but I'm still your mommy and you're still my baby.

217
00:22:15,019 --> 00:22:17,424
Am I gonna be here forever?

218
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:22,008
oh well, you'll grow up, you'll get married

219
00:22:22,208 --> 00:22:24,222
I believe you'll want a home of your own.

220
00:22:24,422 --> 00:22:27,309
No, I won't.
I want to stay here with you.

221
00:22:28,898 --> 00:22:33,061
Well, as far as I'm concerned you
can stay here as long as you like

222
00:22:33,261 --> 00:22:34,546
Good.

223
00:22:34,746 --> 00:22:36,157
Do you know what my name is?

224
00:22:36,409 --> 00:22:38,269
I suppose you've changed it.

225
00:22:38,814 --> 00:22:40,078
The last time.
You promise?

226
00:22:40,278 --> 00:22:41,206
Yeah
Okay, let me hear.

227
00:22:41,406 --> 00:22:49,704
Barbara Ann Cummings
Sally Ali Suzie Doozy light bulb traffic.

228
00:22:50,836 --> 00:22:52,480
Well, that's a fine name, baby

229
00:22:54,488 --> 00:22:56,057
And I'm not a baby anymore.

230
00:22:56,938 --> 00:22:58,109
Today I'm seven.

231
00:22:58,309 --> 00:23:01,271
Well that's seven
precious years you've been mine.

232
00:23:09,224 --> 00:23:11,556
Oh mrs. Burrell?
Yes

233
00:23:11,756 --> 00:23:13,988
I'm mrs. Mazdan from social services.

234
00:23:15,182 --> 00:23:17,197
Oh, come on in!

235
00:23:18,776 --> 00:23:22,089
I hope you're not bringing me another baby!

236
00:23:22,289 --> 00:23:23,907
I have three of them.

237
00:23:24,107 --> 00:23:26,430
Well actually I have great news!

238
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:28,439
We found a home for Barbara.

239
00:23:30,004 --> 00:23:30,800
Barbara?

240
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,727
Yes uh..Barbara Ann Cummings.

241
00:23:32,927 --> 00:23:35,081
Well she's been here a long time!

242
00:23:35,281 --> 00:23:37,320
Barbara's awful old, you know!

243
00:23:37,461 --> 00:23:41,136
I know she's almost 8 but we were
so fortunate in finding a family

244
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:44,821
that specifically
requested a female unadoptable.

245
00:23:45,021 --> 00:23:47,030
There's nothing unadoptable about it.

246
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:49,640
You just forgot about as all you did.

247
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:52,400
I'm afraid I have to agree.

248
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,830
The previous worker left this case in a total shambles.

249
00:23:55,623 --> 00:23:57,287
Now when does the little one get back from school?

250
00:23:57,487 --> 00:24:00,025
About 4:00.

251
00:24:01,114 --> 00:24:03,105
I have in that... program?

252
00:24:03,602 --> 00:24:05,145
the buses are
clear out to concord

253
00:24:05,345 --> 00:24:06,708
Her teachers recommended it,
she's very bright you know

